<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="54" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="9.[813,1452,282,401]" pageId="9" pageNumber="54">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[813,957,282,306]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="54">Diagnosis. –</emphasis>
Resembling 
<taxonomicName authority="Shamshev &amp; Grootaert, 2004" authorityName="Shamshev &amp; Grootaert" authorityYear="2004" box="[1109,1245,283,306]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Microphorella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="papuana" status="new species">
<emphasis box="[1109,1245,283,306]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="54">M. papuana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1263,1401,282,305]" pageId="9" pageNumber="54" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
, but smaller, legs with indistinct pattern, only male abdominal sternite 6 with large, broad process; right surstylus long, narrow.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="55" pageId="9" pageNumber="54" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="9.[813,1452,442,689]" lastBlockId="10.[136,775,193,632]" lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="55" pageId="9" pageNumber="54">
<emphasis box="[813,1034,442,466]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="54">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[813,970,442,466]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="54">Description. –</emphasis>
Male
</emphasis>
body length 
<quantity box="[1180,1309,442,465]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.35" metricValueMax="1.4" metricValueMin="1.3" pageId="9" pageNumber="54" unit="mm" value="1.35" valueMax="1.4" valueMin="1.3">1.3-1.4 mm</quantity>
, wing length 
<quantity box="[813,942,474,497]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.15" metricValueMax="1.2" metricValueMin="1.1" pageId="9" pageNumber="54" unit="mm" value="1.15" valueMax="1.2" valueMin="1.1">1.1-1.2 mm</quantity>
. Head and thorax greyish pollinose, with darkgreen tinge (in some angle of view). Ocellar tubercle with 2 long anterior and 2 very short posterior ocellar bristles. Face in middle somewhat narrower than distance between posterior ocelli. Scutum with 1 postsutural supra-alar bristle. Dorsocentrals represented by 4 long bristles per row. Legs with indistinct pattern: coxae yellowish brown, fore coxa yellowish in apical part; trochanters of all legs brownish yellow; femora yellowish, with brownish tinge, more distinctly brownish dorsally; tibiae yellow; fore tarsus with tarsomeres 1-3 yellow and tarsomeres 4-5 brown, mid and hind tarsi with tarsomeres 1-2 yellow and tarsomeres 3-5 becoming gradually darker (tarsomere 5 brown). Tarsi slender (except tarsomere 5). Wing with basal section of costa bearing 1 short and 1 long bristles. Abdomen with sternite 4 bearing row of long, strong setae on each side (
<figureCitation box="[548,677,449,472]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="9.[114,159,2061,2082]" captionTargetBox="[234,1326,757,2020]" captionTargetId="figure-14@9.[191,1371,690,2063]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figs. 31-35. Microphorella bira, new species, male. 31 – postabdomen (segment 8 and hypopygium not shown), left lateral view, 32 – same, ventral view, 33 – terminalia, right lateral view, 34 – same, left lateral view, 35 – same, ventral view. Scale 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4619502" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4619502/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="55">Figs. 31, 32</figureCitation>
); sternite 5 lacking process, with several ordinary setae, sternite 6 with large broad (viewed ventrally) process; sternite 6 and segment 7 lacking setation. Terminalia (
<figureCitation box="[506,640,545,568]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="9.[114,159,2061,2082]" captionTargetBox="[234,1326,757,2020]" captionTargetId="figure-14@9.[191,1371,690,2063]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figs. 31-35. Microphorella bira, new species, male. 31 – postabdomen (segment 8 and hypopygium not shown), left lateral view, 32 – same, ventral view, 33 – terminalia, right lateral view, 34 – same, left lateral view, 35 – same, ventral view. Scale 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4619502" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4619502/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="55">Figs. 33-35</figureCitation>
) with right surstylus long, rather narrow. Otherwise as in 
<taxonomicName authority="Shamshev &amp; Grootaert, 2004" authorityName="Shamshev &amp; Grootaert" authorityYear="2004" box="[613,768,577,600]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Microphorella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="malaysiana" status="new species">
<emphasis box="[613,768,577,600]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="55">M. malaysiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[136,269,609,632]" pageId="10" pageNumber="55" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4619502" ID-Zenodo-Dep="4619502" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4619502/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="54" startId="9.[114,159,2061,2082]" targetBox="[234,1326,757,2020]" targetPageId="9">
<paragraph blockId="9.[114,1452,2061,2111]" pageId="9" pageNumber="54">
Figs. 31-35. 
<taxonomicName authority="Shamshev &amp; Grootaert, 2004" authorityName="Shamshev &amp; Grootaert" authorityYear="2004" box="[234,419,2061,2082]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Microphorella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bira" status="new species">
<emphasis box="[234,419,2061,2082]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="54">Microphorella bira</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[431,548,2061,2082]" pageId="9" pageNumber="54" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
, male. 31 – postabdomen (segment 8 and hypopygium not shown), left lateral view, 32 – same, ventral view, 33 – terminalia, right lateral view, 34 – same, left lateral view, 35 – same, ventral view. Scale 0.1 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="10.[136,775,673,888]" pageId="10" pageNumber="55">
<emphasis box="[136,217,673,696]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="55">Female</emphasis>
body length 
<quantity box="[363,491,673,696]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.35" metricValueMax="1.4" metricValueMin="1.3" pageId="10" pageNumber="55" unit="mm" value="1.35" valueMax="1.4" valueMin="1.3">1.3-1.4 mm</quantity>
, wing length 
<quantity box="[642,771,673,696]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.25" metricValueMax="1.3" metricValueMin="1.2" pageId="10" pageNumber="55" unit="mm" value="1.25" valueMax="1.3" valueMin="1.2">1.2-1.3 mm</quantity>
. Similar to male except the following characters. Palpus brown, with ordinary setulae. Legs darker, with more distinct pattern; femora largely brownish, paler apically, all tibiae and tarsomeres 1-2 of all tarsi yellowish brown. Postabdomen, including cerci, brown, as in 
<taxonomicName authority="Shamshev &amp; Grootaert, 2004" authorityName="Shamshev &amp; Grootaert" authorityYear="2004" box="[464,626,833,856]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Microphorella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="malaysiana" status="new species">
<emphasis box="[464,626,833,856]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="55">M. malaysiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[642,775,833,856]" pageId="10" pageNumber="55" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
(spermatheca was not studied).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="55" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="10.[136,775,929,1016]" pageId="10" pageNumber="55">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,453,929,953]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="55">Differential diagnosis. –</emphasis>
